ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W3_LibraryBorrowingProgram

Class Name: LibraryBorrowingApp

Difficulty: Level 3 — Object-Oriented Problem Solving

Estimated Time: 60–90 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 64 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Create a console-based library borrowing system.
The program manages books and members.
Users can view books, view members, borrow books, return books,
and check a member's borrowing status.

Program Flow
1. Create Scanner.
2. Create Library.
3. Add several Book and Member objects to Library.
4. Show menu repeatedly.
5. Receive user menu selection.
6. Call the appropriate Library method.
7. Continue until the user selects 0.

Class Responsibilities
LibraryBorrowingApp controls console input and program flow.
Book stores book data and borrowing state.
Member stores member data and borrowing count.
Library manages books, members, search logic, borrowing, and returning.